erience. His philosophy can thus provide precisely what modern European rationalism now so painfully lacks: an understanding and appreciation of the world in which human beings actually make their homes.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mrz 2024) 0aLife. 4aPhilosophy : Ancient Greek Philosophy. 4aPhilosophy : Aristotle. 4aPhilosophy : Phenomenology. 4aPhilosophy : Philosophy. 7aPHILOSOPHY / History & Surveys / Ancient & Classical.2bisacsh40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781438445205?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781438445205423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781438445205/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles